org.semanticweb.rulewerk.core.model.api

Interface SyntaxObject

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Entity
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Conjunction<T>, Fact, Literal, NegativeLiteral, PositiveLiteral, Rule
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractLiteralImpl, ConjunctionImpl, FactImpl, NegativeLiteralImpl, PositiveLiteralImpl, RuleImpl

    public interface SyntaxObject
extends Entity
    General interface for all classes that represent syntactic objects that might contain atomic terms, in particular all kinds of logical formulas. Compound terms (with nested functions) would also be of this type if we had them.
    Author:
    Markus Kroetzsch
